[
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: I'm Steve Mould.",
        "start": 3.276,
        "duration": 1.424
    },
    {
        "text": "And I think we should stop using\npi and start using tau.",
        "start": 4.7,
        "duration": 3.96
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: And I'm\nMatt Parker.",
        "start": 8.66,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "And I think Steve said\nsomething ridiculous.",
        "start": 9.98,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "I think pi is fantastic.",
        "start": 12.62,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "It's wonderful.",
        "start": 14.15,
        "duration": 0.56
    },
    {
        "text": "And even if this was an equal\nrace, we would've been using",
        "start": 14.71,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "both of them.",
        "start": 18.79,
        "duration": 0.34
    },
    {
        "text": "Or even if tau had been\nestablished first, I'm still",
        "start": 19.13,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "pretty pro-pi.",
        "start": 21.73,
        "duration": 0.7
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Wow, that's\nquite a claim.",
        "start": 22.43,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Yes, there's\n[INAUDIBLE].",
        "start": 23.89,
        "duration": 0.7
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: So let's\ntalk about this.",
        "start": 24.59,
        "duration": 0.86
    },
    {
        "text": "So pi is the circle constant.",
        "start": 25.45,
        "duration": 2.586
    },
    {
        "text": "It's the constant that\ndefines a circle.",
        "start": 28.036,
        "duration": 2.524
    },
    {
        "text": "And the argument is--",
        "start": 30.56,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: We're\nagreed so far.",
        "start": 31.25,
        "duration": 1.4
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 32.65,
        "duration": 0.13
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Let's think of a\nreasonable definition of what",
        "start": 32.78,
        "duration": 1.675
    },
    {
        "text": "a circle is.",
        "start": 34.455,
        "duration": 1.525
    },
    {
        "text": "The classic is all points\nequidistant",
        "start": 35.98,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "from a single point.",
        "start": 38.72,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "That distance is the radius.",
        "start": 40.47,
        "duration": 1.72
    },
    {
        "text": "And if you're ever doing maths\nusing circles, you talk about",
        "start": 42.19,
        "duration": 4.97
    },
    {
        "text": "the radius.",
        "start": 47.16,
        "duration": 0.58
    },
    {
        "text": "All your equations about circles\ntalk about the radius.",
        "start": 47.74,
        "duration": 3.925
    },
    {
        "text": "Unless you're an engineer,\nyou use diameter.",
        "start": 51.665,
        "duration": 1.935
    },
    {
        "text": "But as a mathematician,\nyou use the radius.",
        "start": 53.6,
        "duration": 3.37
    },
    {
        "text": "The circle constant should\nsurely be defined in terms of",
        "start": 56.97,
        "duration": 2.93
    },
    {
        "text": "the radius.",
        "start": 59.9,
        "duration": 0.335
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 60.235,
        "duration": 0.255
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: But it isn't pi--",
        "start": 60.49,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "is the circumference\ndivided by the",
        "start": 62.18,
        "duration": 3.05
    },
    {
        "text": "diameter, which is crazy.",
        "start": 65.23,
        "duration": 2.02
    },
    {
        "text": "So the circle constant should\nbe the circumference divided",
        "start": 67.25,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "by the radius.",
        "start": 69.89,
        "duration": 0.95
    },
    {
        "text": "When you do that, you\nget 2 times pi.",
        "start": 70.84,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 72.76,
        "duration": 0.32
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: And so we're not\nsaying let's redefine pi and",
        "start": 73.08,
        "duration": 2.57
    },
    {
        "text": "call it 6.28.",
        "start": 75.65,
        "duration": 4.22
    },
    {
        "text": "But instead--",
        "start": 79.87,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Wow.",
        "start": 80.56,
        "duration": 0.26
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: --we're saying--",
        "start": 80.82,
        "duration": 0.46
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 81.28,
        "duration": 0.54
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Shut up.",
        "start": 81.82,
        "duration": 0.89
    },
    {
        "text": "Instead, we're saying that's\ngoing to be confusing, so",
        "start": 82.71,
        "duration": 2.585
    },
    {
        "text": "let's invent a new constant.",
        "start": 85.295,
        "duration": 0.535
    },
    {
        "text": "And we'll call it tau.",
        "start": 85.83,
        "duration": 0.765
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: To be honest, one\nof the points was quite nice,",
        "start": 86.595,
        "duration": 2.335
    },
    {
        "text": "which is that if you're an\nengineer, you use pi.",
        "start": 88.93,
        "duration": 4.29
    },
    {
        "text": "And in fact, historically, we've\nused pi because when you",
        "start": 93.22,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "measure a circle, the only\ndirect measurement you can",
        "start": 95.62,
        "duration": 3.89
    },
    {
        "text": "make is of the diameter.",
        "start": 99.51,
        "duration": 0.95
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 100.46,
        "duration": 0.33
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: And so that's why\nhistorically we've done that.",
        "start": 100.79,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "And to this day in precision\nengineering we do that.",
        "start": 103.32,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "And yes, you can do some\nvery nice maths with",
        "start": 105.48,
        "duration": 3.53
    },
    {
        "text": "the radius in a circle.",
        "start": 109.01,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "But the only thing\nyou can directly",
        "start": 110.3,
        "duration": 1.43
    },
    {
        "text": "measure is the diameter.",
        "start": 111.73,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "So that's why we've used pi.",
        "start": 112.99,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "People say, oh, but we have\nto put 2 pi into lots of",
        "start": 115.07,
        "duration": 4.06
    },
    {
        "text": "equations, and then\nblah, blah, blah.",
        "start": 119.13,
        "duration": 1.1
    },
    {
        "text": "It's always 2 pi.",
        "start": 120.23,
        "duration": 1.05
    },
    {
        "text": "Why don't we just\nuse tau instead?",
        "start": 121.28,
        "duration": 0.99
    },
    {
        "text": "There are as many fantastic\nequations out there which use",
        "start": 122.27,
        "duration": 4.63
    },
    {
        "text": "just the single pi.",
        "start": 126.9,
        "duration": 0.89
    },
    {
        "text": "And there's no reason\nto bring in 2 pi.",
        "start": 127.79,
        "duration": 1.864
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 129.654,
        "duration": 0.426
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: And so I see\nSteve is holding a pen.",
        "start": 130.08,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "But I have brought my own.",
        "start": 131.78,
        "duration": 0.95
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: [CHUCKLING].",
        "start": 132.73,
        "duration": 0.86
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: So everyone's\nclassic is the e to the i pi",
        "start": 133.59,
        "duration": 3.93
    },
    {
        "text": "job, where e to the i\npi plus 1 equals 0.",
        "start": 137.52,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 142.24,
        "duration": 0.365
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: And that is\nusing a solitary pi",
        "start": 142.605,
        "duration": 2.675
    },
    {
        "text": "out the front there.",
        "start": 145.28,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "And if you want to go\nwild, things like",
        "start": 146.1,
        "duration": 1.97
    },
    {
        "text": "the area of a torus--",
        "start": 148.07,
        "duration": 3.27
    },
    {
        "text": "this is a nice one-- that\nequals pi squared--",
        "start": 151.34,
        "duration": 2.83
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 154.17,
        "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: --outside the major\nradius squared minus the",
        "start": 154.47,
        "duration": 2.73
    },
    {
        "text": "minor radius squared.",
        "start": 157.2,
        "duration": 1.23
    },
    {
        "text": "So I'm still doing things\nin terms of",
        "start": 158.43,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "radiuses or radii or whatever.",
        "start": 161.04,
        "duration": 1.91
    },
    {
        "text": "But the pi squared--\nthat's lovely.",
        "start": 162.95,
        "duration": 1.665
    },
    {
        "text": "What-- you want 4?",
        "start": 164.615,
        "duration": 2.03
    },
    {
        "text": "I mean, how you are going to--",
        "start": 166.645,
        "duration": 0.915
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Yeah, I want--",
        "start": 167.56,
        "duration": 0.46
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Tau squared on 4?",
        "start": 168.02,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: What-- yeah,\nabsolutely-- tau squared on 4.",
        "start": 168.71,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "And I'll explain why.",
        "start": 170.29,
        "duration": 1.11
    },
    {
        "text": "And this is important.",
        "start": 171.4,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, let's just say that Matt has\ncherry-picked a couple of",
        "start": 172.66,
        "duration": 3.663
    },
    {
        "text": "nice equations there.",
        "start": 176.323,
        "duration": 0.687
    },
    {
        "text": "Two things I'd say-- let's look\nat, for example, the area",
        "start": 177.01,
        "duration": 3.61
    },
    {
        "text": "of a circle.",
        "start": 180.62,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "So we're looking at the\narea pi r squared.",
        "start": 181.7,
        "duration": 3.29
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: That's\njust lovely.",
        "start": 184.99,
        "duration": 0.36
    },
    {
        "text": "Look at that.",
        "start": 185.35,
        "duration": 0.39
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 185.74,
        "duration": 0.396
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Yeah, OK-- but\nhere's the problem.",
        "start": 186.136,
        "duration": 2.384
    },
    {
        "text": "Here's the problem.",
        "start": 188.52,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": "If we reframe that in\ntau, that would",
        "start": 189.21,
        "duration": 3.42
    },
    {
        "text": "be tau by 2 r squared.",
        "start": 192.63,
        "duration": 4.43
    },
    {
        "text": "And you think, OK, that's\nless beautiful.",
        "start": 197.06,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "But this tells us something\nimportant.",
        "start": 199.13,
        "duration": 2.685
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 201.815,
        "duration": 0.325
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: This tells\nus something.",
        "start": 202.14,
        "duration": 1.81
    },
    {
        "text": "This is information that you're\nobscuring by using pi.",
        "start": 203.95,
        "duration": 4.15
    },
    {
        "text": "Because you can derive\nthe area--",
        "start": 208.1,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: By simplifying\nyour--",
        "start": 209.86,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 210.86,
        "duration": 0.4
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: No, listen.",
        "start": 211.26,
        "duration": 0.32
    },
    {
        "text": "You can derive the area of\na circle by integrating.",
        "start": 211.58,
        "duration": 3.13
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 214.71,
        "duration": 0.43
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: So you say, OK,\nhere's our full circle.",
        "start": 215.14,
        "duration": 1.87
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's look at the area of this\nlittle strip where the width",
        "start": 217.01,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "of it is delta r.",
        "start": 221.33,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "And this is r going up.",
        "start": 224.07,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "And so this is full\nr or whatever.",
        "start": 226.26,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "So you integrate.",
        "start": 228.33,
        "duration": 1.45
    },
    {
        "text": "The area of this is pi r dr.",
        "start": 229.78,
        "duration": 6.218
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Tau.",
        "start": 235.998,
        "duration": 1.344
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: No, but--",
        "start": 237.342,
        "duration": 1.278
    },
    {
        "text": "sorry, tau, yeah, actually.",
        "start": 238.62,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 240.42,
        "duration": 0.4
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: See, pi's\njust easier to use.",
        "start": 240.82,
        "duration": 2.125
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Shut up.",
        "start": 242.945,
        "duration": 0.885
    },
    {
        "text": "And then you end up with\n1/2 tau r squared.",
        "start": 243.83,
        "duration": 3.73
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 247.56,
        "duration": 0.29
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: And so that 1/2\ntells you something.",
        "start": 247.85,
        "duration": 2.54
    },
    {
        "text": "It tells you you've done an\nintegration to get there.",
        "start": 250.39,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 252.09,
        "duration": 0.26
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: And an equation\nlike this obscures it.",
        "start": 252.35,
        "duration": 1.766
    },
    {
        "text": "Similarly, with this, if you had\ntau squared over 4, that",
        "start": 254.116,
        "duration": 2.358
    },
    {
        "text": "would tell you something.",
        "start": 256.474,
        "duration": 1.336
    },
    {
        "text": "This equation here-- let's\njust reframe that.",
        "start": 257.81,
        "duration": 2.269
    },
    {
        "text": "e to the i tau minus\n1 equals 0.",
        "start": 260.079,
        "duration": 5.431
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 265.51,
        "duration": 0.23
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: And the great\nthing is that is a full",
        "start": 265.74,
        "duration": 2.29
    },
    {
        "text": "circle, right?",
        "start": 268.03,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "If you want to go through half a\ncircle, then it's e to the i",
        "start": 269.35,
        "duration": 3.57
    },
    {
        "text": "tau over 2.",
        "start": 272.92,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "If you want to go a quarter\nof a circle, it's e to",
        "start": 274.38,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "the i tau by 4.",
        "start": 277.12,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 278.9,
        "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: The pi\nis confusing.",
        "start": 279.2,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "It's especially confusing\nfor children when",
        "start": 280.38,
        "duration": 1.595
    },
    {
        "text": "they're learning as well.",
        "start": 281.975,
        "duration": 1.145
    },
    {
        "text": "A full circle is 2 pi?",
        "start": 283.12,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so that half\na circle is pi.",
        "start": 285.84,
        "duration": 3.19
    },
    {
        "text": "A quarter of a circle\nis pi by 2.",
        "start": 289.03,
        "duration": 2.51
    },
    {
        "text": "So there's always this\nfactor of 2--",
        "start": 291.54,
        "duration": 2.05
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 293.59,
        "duration": 0.355
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: --that you've got\nto keep in your mind when",
        "start": 293.945,
        "duration": 1.725
    },
    {
        "text": "you're doing calculations.",
        "start": 295.67,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "And actually, if you're a\nseasoned mathematician, you're",
        "start": 297.27,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "probably always thinking in\nterms of 2 pi, anyway.",
        "start": 299.58,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 301.8,
        "duration": 0.41
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: And so let's just\nstop thinking in terms of 2 pi",
        "start": 302.21,
        "duration": 2.18
    },
    {
        "text": "and start thinking\nin terms of tau.",
        "start": 304.39,
        "duration": 0.97
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: This is the\nhypocrisies of tau.",
        "start": 305.36,
        "duration": 0.8
    },
    {
        "text": "You want halves here.",
        "start": 306.16,
        "duration": 1.19
    },
    {
        "text": "You don't want halves\nover there.",
        "start": 307.35,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 308.64,
        "duration": 0.52
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: I want halves here\nbecause the half tells",
        "start": 309.16,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "you something.",
        "start": 311.62,
        "duration": 0.26
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 311.88,
        "duration": 0.14
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: This works\nout just as nicely.",
        "start": 312.02,
        "duration": 1.27
    },
    {
        "text": "Because if you want to\nintegrate, and you've got your",
        "start": 313.29,
        "duration": 1.87
    },
    {
        "text": "2 pi r dr, then you\nget a wonderful",
        "start": 315.16,
        "duration": 5.75
    },
    {
        "text": "thing you can simplify.",
        "start": 320.91,
        "duration": 1.05
    },
    {
        "text": "Because you end up with\nthis-- r squared--",
        "start": 321.96,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Yeah, so in\nthis particular case--",
        "start": 323.55,
        "duration": 1.2
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: --and you\nend up with a--",
        "start": 324.75,
        "duration": 1.02
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 325.77,
        "duration": 0.16
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: So in this\nparticular case--",
        "start": 325.93,
        "duration": 0.14
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: --2 pi and\nthe 1/2 simplifies.",
        "start": 326.07,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 328.71,
        "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Yeah, yeah.",
        "start": 329.01,
        "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Pi r--\nthat's just--",
        "start": 329.31,
        "duration": 1.42
    },
    {
        "text": "there's nowhere else in maths\nwhere you say, you know what?",
        "start": 330.73,
        "duration": 3.49
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's not simplify it.",
        "start": 334.22,
        "duration": 0.88
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's leave it in a more\ncomplicated form because it--",
        "start": 335.1,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: No, but in fact,\nthis is the one case where you",
        "start": 338.08,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "think, actually it's useful to\nhave a 2 there because we can",
        "start": 340.86,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "cancel later.",
        "start": 343.42,
        "duration": 0.88
    },
    {
        "text": "Most other cases you don't get\nto do that cancel because",
        "start": 344.3,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "you're not dividing\nby 2 later on.",
        "start": 346.74,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 349.05,
        "duration": 0.28
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: In most cases, you\nend up with an equation",
        "start": 349.33,
        "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
        "text": "that's got 2 pi in it.",
        "start": 351.15,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: A lot of smart\npeople, who I know you",
        "start": 352.37,
        "duration": 2.11
    },
    {
        "text": "respect-- and I know\nyou respect the guy",
        "start": 354.48,
        "duration": 1.49
    },
    {
        "text": "sitting next to you--",
        "start": 355.97,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: [CHUCKLING].",
        "start": 356.97,
        "duration": 0.4
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: --make the case--",
        "start": 357.37,
        "duration": 0.745
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: That's correct.",
        "start": 358.115,
        "duration": 0.445
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Professionally.",
        "start": 358.56,
        "duration": 0.89
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: A lot of smart\npeople make the case for tau.",
        "start": 359.45,
        "duration": 2.445
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Yeah.",
        "start": 361.895,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: How do you explain\ntheir reasoning?",
        "start": 362.675,
        "duration": 3.875
    },
    {
        "text": "How do you--",
        "start": 366.55,
        "duration": 1.216
    },
    {
        "text": "I mean, you don't think\nSteve's an idiot.",
        "start": 367.766,
        "duration": 1.424
    },
    {
        "text": "But he has this feeling about\ntau that you disagree with.",
        "start": 369.19,
        "duration": 3.96
    },
    {
        "text": "What's different about his\nthinking to yours?",
        "start": 373.15,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: You know what?",
        "start": 374.59,
        "duration": 0.61
    },
    {
        "text": "A lot of people do have very\ngood arguments for tau.",
        "start": 375.2,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "And a lot of people have very\ngood arguments for pi.",
        "start": 378.2,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "And there is a wonderful\nthing--",
        "start": 380.21,
        "duration": 3.49
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't know.",
        "start": 383.7,
        "duration": 0.56
    },
    {
        "text": "I think people like the fact\nthat it's different and that",
        "start": 384.26,
        "duration": 2.71
    },
    {
        "text": "they're going, oh, whoa,\nwhoa, whoa-- everyone",
        "start": 386.97,
        "duration": 1.05
    },
    {
        "text": "else has got it wrong.",
        "start": 388.02,
        "duration": 0.89
    },
    {
        "text": "We can change this.",
        "start": 388.91,
        "duration": 1.02
    },
    {
        "text": "And tau is better.",
        "start": 389.93,
        "duration": 0.705
    },
    {
        "text": "And oh, people try and\ndo maths and they",
        "start": 390.635,
        "duration": 3.265
    },
    {
        "text": "think pi's all that.",
        "start": 393.9,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "No, they're wrong.",
        "start": 395.2,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "But I don't think there's any\ngreat advantage other than it",
        "start": 396.32,
        "duration": 6.17
    },
    {
        "text": "can be a bit more exclusive to\nsay, oh, we're all over tau--",
        "start": 402.49,
        "duration": 2.54
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 405.03,
        "duration": 0.29
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: --when I\nthink pi works just",
        "start": 405.32,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "as well in all cases.",
        "start": 407.21,
        "duration": 0.87
    },
    {
        "text": "It's got the--",
        "start": 408.08,
        "duration": 1.085
    },
    {
        "text": "I know--",
        "start": 409.165,
        "duration": 1.295
    },
    {
        "text": "historical--",
        "start": 410.46,
        "duration": 1.055
    },
    {
        "text": "the fact that it's got a bit\nof heritage doesn't mean we",
        "start": 411.515,
        "duration": 1.995
    },
    {
        "text": "should keep it around\nnecessarily.",
        "start": 413.51,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "But it's worked for\na very long time.",
        "start": 415.1,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "And it's there for very\ngood reasons.",
        "start": 416.64,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 417.98,
        "duration": 1.24
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Nothing people have\nthrown at me in terms of",
        "start": 419.22,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "tau, saying it's better--",
        "start": 422.34,
        "duration": 2.9
    },
    {
        "text": "you gain as much as\nyou lose from--",
        "start": 425.24,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 426.95,
        "duration": 0.22
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: --switching from--\nboth of them have their",
        "start": 427.17,
        "duration": 1.79
    },
    {
        "text": "disadvantages and their\nadvantages.",
        "start": 428.96,
        "duration": 0.97
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 429.93,
        "duration": 0.06
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: I don't think\nthere's enough for an entire",
        "start": 429.99,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "overhaul of the subject because\npeople think, oh,",
        "start": 431.82,
        "duration": 3.38
    },
    {
        "text": "what, this particular equation\nlooks a bit nicer.",
        "start": 435.2,
        "duration": 2.18
    },
    {
        "text": "Oh, but we've lost the fact that\nyou get negative numbers",
        "start": 437.38,
        "duration": 2.95
    },
    {
        "text": "in Euler's identity.",
        "start": 440.33,
        "duration": 2.36
    },
    {
        "text": "And even your arguments\nwith circles--",
        "start": 442.69,
        "duration": 3.49
    },
    {
        "text": "this is my clincher.",
        "start": 446.18,
        "duration": 0.91
    },
    {
        "text": "This is why I genuinely\nthink pi is nicer.",
        "start": 447.09,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "If you've got tau, right?",
        "start": 449.67,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "If you do tau radians--",
        "start": 451.68,
        "duration": 2.05
    },
    {
        "text": "you do an entire revolution--",
        "start": 453.73,
        "duration": 1.45
    },
    {
        "text": "you end up right back\nwhere you started.",
        "start": 455.18,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "Tau gets you nowhere, right?",
        "start": 457.27,
        "duration": 1.086
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 458.356,
        "duration": 0.406
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: [CHUCKLING].",
        "start": 458.762,
        "duration": 1.698
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: With pi, if you\ndo pi radians, you actually",
        "start": 460.46,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "get somewhere.",
        "start": 462.99,
        "duration": 0.88
    },
    {
        "text": "And I think if you want a unit\nto measure things, the unit",
        "start": 463.87,
        "duration": 3.74
    },
    {
        "text": "shouldn't be the whole thing.",
        "start": 467.61,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 468.91,
        "duration": 0.285
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: What?",
        "start": 469.195,
        "duration": 0.285
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHING].",
        "start": 469.48,
        "duration": 0.4
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: A unit should\nbe a section of it.",
        "start": 469.88,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "And so it's more nuanced.",
        "start": 471.82,
        "duration": 1.45
    },
    {
        "text": "And for that reason--",
        "start": 473.27,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Oh, then\nin that case--",
        "start": 474.09,
        "duration": 0.84
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: I think\npi is better.",
        "start": 474.93,
        "duration": 1.03
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: --divide it\nby-- you know--360.",
        "start": 475.96,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 477.04,
        "duration": 0.37
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Now you've\njust gone too far.",
        "start": 477.41,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": "No one would use that\nkind of a unit.",
        "start": 478.8,
        "duration": 2.355
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: Steve--",
        "start": 481.155,
        "duration": 0.485
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Yeah.",
        "start": 481.64,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: I've heard\nyou talk a little bit.",
        "start": 482.42,
        "duration": 2.85
    },
    {
        "text": "And you seem to have an\nenjoyment of the history of",
        "start": 485.27,
        "duration": 2.63
    },
    {
        "text": "mathematics.",
        "start": 487.9,
        "duration": 0.65
    },
    {
        "text": "Maths is beautiful and pure.",
        "start": 488.55,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "But it's also got\ngreat stories.",
        "start": 490.38,
        "duration": 1.605
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Yeah.",
        "start": 491.985,
        "duration": 0.585
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: Why are you willing\nto ditch pi, which is",
        "start": 492.57,
        "duration": 2.11
    },
    {
        "text": "one of our most important\nclinged-to, loved stories?",
        "start": 494.68,
        "duration": 4.34
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Don't overstate\nmy case here, all right?",
        "start": 499.02,
        "duration": 2.236
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: One word--\nprogress.",
        "start": 501.256,
        "duration": 1.574
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 502.83,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: The historical\npoint is a good one.",
        "start": 504.11,
        "duration": 2.29
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 506.4,
        "duration": 0.49
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Historically, we\nused to sacrifice goats.",
        "start": 506.89,
        "duration": 3.39
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 510.28,
        "duration": 0.39
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: And I think we\nshould keep doing that.",
        "start": 510.67,
        "duration": 1.724
    },
    {
        "text": "No--",
        "start": 512.394,
        "duration": 1.116
    },
    {
        "text": "so you can't just cling to\nsomething because of history.",
        "start": 513.51,
        "duration": 2.549
    },
    {
        "text": "Having said that, one argument\nagainst tau is that pi is very",
        "start": 516.059,
        "duration": 5.911
    },
    {
        "text": "well established.",
        "start": 521.97,
        "duration": 0.569
    },
    {
        "text": "And we'll just never\nreplace it.",
        "start": 522.539,
        "duration": 2.371
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 524.91,
        "duration": 0.29
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: The strong argument\nfor me is that tau is",
        "start": 525.2,
        "duration": 3.81
    },
    {
        "text": "more intuitive.",
        "start": 529.01,
        "duration": 1.06
    },
    {
        "text": "And so from an educational\npoint of view--",
        "start": 530.07,
        "duration": 2.35
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 532.42,
        "duration": 0.51
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: --in terms of\nunderstanding circles and",
        "start": 532.93,
        "duration": 1.37
    },
    {
        "text": "working with circles, tau\nmakes more sense.",
        "start": 534.3,
        "duration": 3.21
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: Maybe just\ncall it a circle.",
        "start": 537.51,
        "duration": 1.615
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: OK, Steve--",
        "start": 539.125,
        "duration": 1.975
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: When you're trying\nto teach kids angles,",
        "start": 541.1,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "and you go, what\nangle is this?",
        "start": 543.2,
        "duration": 1.79
    },
    {
        "text": "All of it.",
        "start": 544.99,
        "duration": 0.54
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 545.53,
        "duration": 0.365
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: That's just\nall the way round.",
        "start": 545.895,
        "duration": 2.925
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: But then you start\ndealing with radians.",
        "start": 548.82,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: And then you\nget half the circle.",
        "start": 550.08,
        "duration": 1.13
    },
    {
        "text": "It's called a circle.",
        "start": 551.21,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: Steve, if I made\nyou education minister of the",
        "start": 552.03,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "world tomorrow, what would you\ndo about this situation?",
        "start": 554.12,
        "duration": 3.59
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Well,\nhere's the thing.",
        "start": 557.71,
        "duration": 0.95
    },
    {
        "text": "I think you can actually\nslowly bring it in.",
        "start": 558.66,
        "duration": 4.21
    },
    {
        "text": "Because you can use pi and\ntau at the same time.",
        "start": 562.87,
        "duration": 3.01
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 565.88,
        "duration": 0.44
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Because wherever\nyou see 2 pi,",
        "start": 566.32,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "you can write tau.",
        "start": 568.6,
        "duration": 0.79
    },
    {
        "text": "So you don't have\nto change any--",
        "start": 569.39,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "you don't have to suddenly\noverhaul textbooks and",
        "start": 571.19,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "redefine pi.",
        "start": 573.38,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "You can bring it in slowly.",
        "start": 575.66,
        "duration": 1.15
    },
    {
        "text": "And so if I was education\nminister of the world-- and I",
        "start": 576.81,
        "duration": 2.73
    },
    {
        "text": "hope to be one day--",
        "start": 579.54,
        "duration": 2.415
    },
    {
        "text": "you can bring it\nin very slowly.",
        "start": 581.955,
        "duration": 2.221
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: Matt, your argument\nseems to be that the",
        "start": 584.176,
        "duration": 4.034
    },
    {
        "text": "tau people aren't wrong.",
        "start": 588.21,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "It's just a bit needless.",
        "start": 590.41,
        "duration": 1.55
    },
    {
        "text": "It's extra work--",
        "start": 591.96,
        "duration": 0.86
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: They're\ninsufficiently right.",
        "start": 592.82,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 594.18,
        "duration": 0.27
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: [LAUGHING].",
        "start": 594.45,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: So what's wrong\nwith education minister for",
        "start": 595.71,
        "duration": 2.265
    },
    {
        "text": "the world there next to you\nslowly bringing in tau?",
        "start": 597.975,
        "duration": 2.355
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: I have no problem\nwith tau sitting alongside pi.",
        "start": 603.05,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 605.75,
        "duration": 0.28
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: I have\nno problem with--",
        "start": 606.03,
        "duration": 0.86
    },
    {
        "text": "I think it's very important--\nyou're right-- to teach",
        "start": 606.89,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "radians in terms of it's a\nwhole circle, and we're",
        "start": 608.75,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "splitting it up into smaller\namounts, and how it links to",
        "start": 610.69,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "wonderful things like this.",
        "start": 613.06,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "But you never see anyone who's\nplugging tau in and going, you",
        "start": 614.34,
        "duration": 4.365
    },
    {
        "text": "know what, this would\nbe useful as well.",
        "start": 618.705,
        "duration": 1.445
    },
    {
        "text": "They're always like,\npi is wrong.",
        "start": 620.15,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "And I'm like, well,\npi is not wrong.",
        "start": 621.9,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "STEVE MOULD: Pi is not wrong.",
        "start": 623.02,
        "duration": 0.264
    },
    {
        "text": "No, I know.",
        "start": 623.284,
        "duration": 0.136
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: It's perfectly\nserviceable.",
        "start": 623.42,
        "duration": 1.855
    },
    {
        "text": "It's worked a treat.",
        "start": 625.275,
        "duration": 1.465
    },
    {
        "text": "And it's a wonderful concept.",
        "start": 626.74,
        "duration": 1.21
    },
    {
        "text": "And I think genuinely it's got\na lot more going for it for",
        "start": 627.95,
        "duration": 3.93
    },
    {
        "text": "doing maths than tau.",
        "start": 631.88,
        "duration": 1.61
    },
    {
        "text": "But there's many things where\nyou could say historically--",
        "start": 633.49,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "like, why don't we\ncount in base 12?",
        "start": 636.02,
        "duration": 2.095
    },
    {
        "text": "That would be nicer.",
        "start": 638.115,
        "duration": 2.225
    },
    {
        "text": "But we don't.",
        "start": 640.34,
        "duration": 0.33
    },
    {
        "text": "We count in base 10, which, I\nadmit, I would almost say base",
        "start": 640.67,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "12 has more advantages if we\nswitch to that than if we",
        "start": 643.45,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "switch to tau.",
        "start": 645.67,
        "duration": 0.79
    },
    {
        "text": "[RINGING]",
        "start": 646.46,
        "duration": 0.21
    },
    {
        "text": "MATT PARKER: So why are we\ngetting so emotional about our",
        "start": 646.67,
        "duration": 1.685
    },
    {
        "text": "irrationals when we could be a\nbit more rational about our",
        "start": 648.355,
        "duration": 2.455
    },
    {
        "text": "base systems?",
        "start": 650.81,
        "duration": 0.73
    },
    {
